00:51.324 --> 01:02.320
Vince Lombardi, John Wooden, Whelan Jennings, and Jesus.

01:02.340 --> 01:02.861
Say that again.

01:03.762 --> 01:06.386
Vince Lombardi, John Wooden,

01:08.098 --> 01:11.002
Whaling Jennings and Jesus.

01:12.024 --> 01:17.612
Now, before you start trying to connect the dots, let me just share with you a little about each of them.

01:17.672 --> 01:22.098
For those of you who may be not totally familiar with all of them, of course, besides Jesus.

01:23.720 --> 01:27.846
Vince Lombardi, of course, the legendary coach of the Green Bay Packers in 1961.

01:28.127 --> 01:36.018
The Packers were coming off of a loss in the NFL title game to the Philadelphia Eagles.

01:36.290 --> 01:50.732
As they opened training camp that summer, players were on the edge of their seat wondering what Coach Lombardi had come up with, what strategy, what inspiration he would use to get them over the championship hump.

01:51.433 --> 02:05.074
And as they opened camp, he walked to the front of his players who were waiting with bated breath and he held in his hand a football and to inspire them to greatness, he said, gentlemen, this

02:05.698 --> 02:06.459
is a football.

02:08.402 --> 02:15.593
Wide receiver Max McGee was in the back of the crowd and he said, wait a minute coach slow down, you're going too fast.

02:15.613 --> 02:32.018
John Wooden, John Wooden in 1963, 64 season would begin a run at UCLA winning 10 championships in 12 years, a record which will never be surpassed.

02:32.610 --> 02:35.413
Unless it happens here with Coach Beard at the University of Texas.

02:35.493 --> 02:48.026
But along the way, John Wooden coached some of the greatest college talent to ever play the game, names like Lou Elsinder, who became Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, Bill Walton.

02:48.446 --> 02:50.509
The list goes on and on and on.

02:50.549 --> 02:59.538
And yet with this kind of talent, year after year after year, Coach Wooden began every single season by sitting this

02:59.906 --> 03:13.680
assembled world-class talent in the bleachers in the UCLA gymnasium, sitting them down and teaching them every single year how to put on socks and shoes.

03:15.001 --> 03:16.803
That's how he started every single season.

03:17.684 --> 03:22.008
And he would say, this is how you put on socks so that you don't create blisters.

03:22.088 --> 03:24.511
Then you lace up your shoes in this way.

03:25.091 --> 03:27.954
And it was from that foundation that he would build

03:28.258 --> 03:31.622
a championship dynasty that will never be surpassed.

03:33.044 --> 03:38.630
Whalen Jennings, king of the outlaw country music movement.

03:38.650 --> 03:48.361
In 1977, he immortalized a microscopic Texas town that seven years before had closed their post office.

03:48.401 --> 03:49.182
It was so small.

03:50.183 --> 03:53.067
I'm talking, of course, about Luke and Bach, Texas.

03:54.048 --> 03:56.050
And in this song, Whalen

03:56.130 --> 04:06.204
encourages a fictitious couple focused on their finances and keeping up with the Joneses to get back to the basics of love.

04:06.905 --> 04:07.806
You know the song.

04:09.509 --> 04:18.421
Jesus, I'm gonna get there in just a minute, but what I wanna do is share with you the thread that ties all of these icons together.

04:19.282 --> 04:24.850
They all shared a fanatical focus on the fundamentals.

04:24.994 --> 04:50.610
Whatever the arena might have been, if you go back through history, generals and pastors, coaches and politicos have preached the undeniable link between victory and fundamentals, success, and whatever arena you wanna talk about and paying attention to the basics, focusing on the fundamentals.

04:51.266 --> 05:04.661
as we continue this series family style and we continue to look at God's design, God's desire for the foundational, elemental building block of culture and society in the world, the family.

05:05.903 --> 05:19.218
I think it's imperative that we share this fundamental, fanatical focus on the fundamentals, that we remember the basics of what it is all about.

05:19.682 --> 05:23.207
We've started with kind of a high altitude view.

05:23.608 --> 05:32.120
Last week, Whitney taught us so beautifully about parenting and what that shows us about who God is and how we interact with Him, but also how to parent in the real world.

05:32.962 --> 05:38.830
But today we're going to focus on the most foundational relationship in the world.

05:39.511 --> 05:46.642
I'm talking, of course, about marriage, this centerpiece, this

05:46.978 --> 05:54.007
Keystone lynch pin of the family as the marriage goes so goes the family.

05:54.047 --> 06:05.822
Now, we've already said throughout the series that it is entirely possible for a marriage to fail or to not be everything God designed and desires it to be and God to step in and fill in the blanks.

06:05.862 --> 06:07.825
That happens all the time.

06:08.285 --> 06:14.173
Unfortunately, it's necessary and fortunately by the grace of God, His grace is sufficient.

06:14.193 --> 06:15.314
We've established that.

06:15.714 --> 06:20.400
And I know also that already some may be thinking to themselves, man, this isn't for me.

06:21.001 --> 06:22.222
I'm not married.

06:22.543 --> 06:26.247
I don't have any interest in being married anytime soon or maybe ever at all.

06:27.008 --> 06:30.292
But I wanna encourage you especially, don't check out on this thing.

06:30.693 --> 06:38.302
As a matter of fact, God says repeatedly throughout the Bible that it is single followers of Christ.

06:39.183 --> 06:44.530
Followers of Christ who are not married, who help us to understand, who help us to appreciate

06:44.642 --> 06:51.109
marriage and what it is, but also that as a single follower of Christ, you hold a special place.

06:51.129 --> 06:55.675
You hold a special office in the body of Christ.

06:55.715 --> 06:57.236
I'm gonna get to that in just a minute.

06:58.217 --> 07:00.981
But real quickly, I wanna go back to Jesus.

07:01.681 --> 07:07.308
I wanna go back to Jesus in what he taught about this fanatical focus on the fundamentals.

07:08.189 --> 07:10.531
If you have your Bibles, look in Matthew chapter 19.

07:11.132 --> 07:12.754
In Matthew 19,

07:13.026 --> 07:16.913
Jesus is again confronted by the Pharisees.

07:17.033 --> 07:28.254
The Pharisees were a sect of Judaism alive and well during Jesus' day, and they were kind of the self-appointed religious rules and regulations watchdogs.

07:29.015 --> 07:32.882
And over and over again, they tried to, they tried to

07:33.250 --> 07:34.311
trap Jesus.

07:34.391 --> 07:44.621
They would engage Him in doctrinal discussions, hoping to discredit and denigrate His influence with the common folks that they tried to keep under wraps.

07:45.582 --> 07:56.793
And in this particular exchange in Matthew 19, they used the subject of marriage, or maybe more specifically, the subject of divorce in their attempt to trap Jesus.

07:57.734 --> 07:59.756
Here's how Matthew records this exchange.

07:59.936 --> 08:01.778
Matthew 19, we're starting in verse three.

08:03.010 --> 08:06.595
The Bible says some Pharisees came and tried to trap him with this question.

08:07.696 --> 08:11.141
Should a man be allowed to divorce his wife for just any reason?

08:12.723 --> 08:14.706
Haven't you read the scriptures Jesus replied?

08:14.746 --> 08:22.216
They record that from the beginning God made them male and female.

08:23.378 --> 08:32.050
And he said, this explains why a man leaves his father and mother and is joined to his wife and the two are united into one.

08:32.706 --> 08:41.380
Since they are no longer two, but one, let no one split apart what God has joined together.

08:42.782 --> 08:44.225
It's a fascinating exchange.

08:44.525 --> 08:47.510
They come to him talking about divorce and he goes back to Genesis.

08:48.512 --> 08:56.905
It's as if Jesus says to the Pharisees, and for that matter to you and to me, this is a family football.

08:57.586 --> 08:59.890
He says, this is the bottom

08:59.970 --> 09:07.183
before we even start talking about divorce, let's talk about what marriage really and truly is.

09:08.104 --> 09:11.110
And he goes back to the beginning and he says, don't you remember?

09:11.150 --> 09:12.552
You've read the Bible, right?

09:13.254 --> 09:20.647
Kind of a little, mmm, dig at the Pharisees and he goes, remember God created us male and female.

09:20.707 --> 09:24.754
In the image of God, he created them male and female.

09:25.410 --> 09:43.096
And that's why people come together as husband and wife, because it is in the image of God that men carry parts of God's image, but women, thankfully, carry other parts of God's image that we don't share.

09:43.316 --> 09:52.510
And the clear teaching of Christ, the clear teaching of the Bible, and you're gonna wanna write this down because it's really, really important.

09:53.752 --> 09:55.314
Men and women.

09:56.962 --> 09:57.623
are different.

09:59.726 --> 10:00.167
I've said it.

10:00.287 --> 10:02.290
I'm just going to put that out there.

10:03.352 --> 10:09.941
Men and women are different by the grace of God.

10:11.043 --> 10:15.149
And this is foundational.

10:15.249 --> 10:18.434
It is fundamental to marriage.

10:18.474 --> 10:21.378
It is fundamental to the family.

10:22.180 --> 10:26.546
I think sometimes fundamental gets a bad rap as if fundamental means

10:26.722 --> 10:32.151
elementary or remedial, or sometimes it gets used to mean legalistic.

10:32.632 --> 10:36.478
But the word fundamental really just means foundational.

10:36.758 --> 10:38.922
That's where the word comes from in the Latin.

10:39.142 --> 10:40.705
It just means a foundation.

10:41.366 --> 10:54.066
So if we ignore fundamentals, if we discount fundamentals, what we're really doing is compromising and corrupting the integrity of the structure of whatever it is we may be talking about.

10:54.530 --> 11:12.167
The fundamentals of marriage means that God in his wisdom and grace and truth brought together men and women in marriage, man and woman to represent him, to bear his image.

11:12.888 --> 11:15.391
That's why this thing called marriage is so powerful.

11:15.471 --> 11:16.632
It's why it's so beautiful.

11:16.672 --> 11:17.953
It's why it is so rich.

11:18.814 --> 11:22.898
And Jesus is trying to get the Pharisees to take their eyes

11:23.426 --> 11:28.191
off of the spec and see the entire forest.

11:28.211 --> 11:30.853
Pull back and look at what God has done.

11:30.893 --> 11:32.815
Look at what God intends.

11:33.896 --> 11:42.784
Going back to the conversation about those of our church family who are not married, who maybe don't want to be married or are not married right now.

11:44.106 --> 11:50.371
Did you know the Hebrews chapter 13 verse 4 says, marriage should be honored by all.

11:51.092 --> 11:53.074
And the marriage bed kept pure.

11:53.570 --> 11:56.973
for God will judge all the sexually immoral.

11:58.014 --> 12:08.705
The reason that that is so profound, the reason that God is so serious about sexual immorality is because it goes to the very core of representing his character and his nature.

12:09.466 --> 12:14.971
So when we compromise in this arena, we're compromising the image of God we were created to bear.

12:15.732 --> 12:18.214
It is a big, big deal.

12:19.295 --> 12:22.258
If you are single, you're in some great company.

12:22.818 --> 12:23.639
You're in great company.

12:23.699 --> 12:27.905
The Apostle Paul who wrote more than two thirds of the New Testament.

12:28.346 --> 12:31.169
The Apostle Paul himself was single.

12:31.690 --> 12:34.975
As a matter of fact, he said he was better off because he was not married.

12:34.995 --> 12:37.738
He was able to focus more on the things of God.

12:37.758 --> 12:39.481
Look at 1 Corinthians chapter seven.

12:39.501 --> 12:45.809
1 Corinthians seven, this is the Apostle Paul under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God writing.

12:45.829 --> 12:49.234
And he says, now I say to those who aren't married and to widows.

12:49.922 --> 12:53.107
It's better to stay unmarried just as I am.

12:54.189 --> 12:56.753
But if they can't control themselves, they should go ahead and marry.

12:56.813 --> 12:59.677
It is better to marry than to burn with lust.

13:00.699 --> 13:01.820
Then skip down to verse 35.

13:01.860 --> 13:04.064
Verse 35, this is so important.

13:05.226 --> 13:10.013
He says, I am saying all of this for your benefit, not to place restrictions on you.

13:10.694 --> 13:18.386
I want you to do whatever will help you serve the Lord best with as few

13:18.530 --> 13:20.752
distractions as possible.

13:23.155 --> 13:28.640
What an incredible word of encouragement and value to those who are single.

13:28.660 --> 13:34.546
We need to understand that marriage is not the be all and end all of the human experience.

13:34.566 --> 13:43.134
It's significant, it's important, but ultimately, whether you're married or whether you're single, the question is not about are you in love?

13:44.236 --> 13:46.738
Do you feel that quiver in your liver or

13:46.978 --> 13:48.460
Are you attracted to them?

13:48.580 --> 13:49.842
Are you compatible?

13:49.922 --> 13:51.144
Do you wanna have children?

13:51.305 --> 13:52.747
None, those things are important.

13:52.827 --> 13:54.109
Don't mistake me.

13:55.371 --> 13:56.913
But ultimately, what did he say?

13:56.933 --> 14:04.004
He goes, I'm telling you this so that you can figure out what is the best way for you to serve the Lord?

14:04.284 --> 14:07.289
How do you serve the Lord best?

14:08.170 --> 14:09.031
Now let me ask you a question.

14:09.091 --> 14:12.497
How many of us in the church family are married?

14:12.537 --> 14:14.440
Can I see a show of hands if you are married?

14:14.560 --> 14:16.082
Keep your hands up if you would, thank you.

14:16.866 --> 14:30.662
Now, how many of us, let's say in the last week, have been distracted to use Paul's word, but keep you guys up, that's okay.

14:30.682 --> 14:35.007
How many of us have been distracted by our spouse?

14:38.230 --> 14:42.936
I mean, there've been a couple of times where I was like, what does Julie want?

14:44.057 --> 14:44.978
What is she thinking?

14:45.666 --> 14:49.472
And in those moments, I have not been thinking about how I can best serve the Lord.

14:50.633 --> 14:52.977
I'm thinking, what the heck?

14:54.799 --> 14:55.360
That happens.

14:56.562 --> 14:58.064
That's what Paul's saying here.

14:58.885 --> 15:03.212
So please understand, if you're single, we are so grateful for you.

15:04.033 --> 15:05.936
We so value you.

15:06.236 --> 15:12.946
You have such a special place in the church, the family of faith and

15:13.666 --> 15:15.829
marriage should be honored by all.

15:16.550 --> 15:24.082
The fact is that most people, most, not all, but most, over 50%, desire at some point to get married.

15:25.023 --> 15:36.220
And when we have that desire, when we think God is leading us to that, then we have to adopt this fanatical focus on the fundamentals.

15:36.821 --> 15:43.090
We have to understand what it is that God is up to, what He is trying to accomplish in and through,

15:43.234 --> 15:48.140
marriage, as the Bible says, men and women are different.

15:49.001 --> 15:49.882
Men and women are different.

15:49.922 --> 15:57.670
I've thought for years, women who try to compete with men are aiming way too low.

15:59.412 --> 16:05.099
I mean, as we like to say, you know, everybody says, you know, you got to set the bar, set the bar high, set the bar high.

16:05.699 --> 16:09.524
If women, you're competing with men, the bar is on the floor.

16:10.685 --> 16:11.506
Think about this.

16:11.938 --> 16:22.551
When God created man, just man, he looked in and he said, it's not good for the man to be alone.

16:22.571 --> 16:41.394
I will create for him a helper, someone suitable, someone to complete him, and then bone at his bone, flesh of his flesh from a rib, not from the head so that she wouldn't dominate, not from the foot, so that he would dominate side by side, he created

16:41.826 --> 16:44.248
Woman, woman.

16:45.710 --> 16:57.641
Ephesians chapter five gives us a complete road map as to how husbands and wives are to view their roles within marriage.

16:57.681 --> 17:00.624
What we're, what we're to do is we focus on the fundamentals.

17:00.684 --> 17:04.808
It's one thing to say that we're different, but then you gotta say, what do we do?

17:05.829 --> 17:09.372
If marriage is gonna be honored by all, how do we go about this?

17:09.493 --> 17:10.994
What does it look like?

17:11.074 --> 17:13.457
Do we pull this off?

17:14.479 --> 17:18.885
Now, I'm gonna begin with husbands.

17:19.686 --> 17:27.898
If Ephesians chapter five starts with wives and we'll get to the ladies, but I'm gonna begin with husbands and I think you'll understand why as we go through this.

17:28.199 --> 17:31.443
Look at Ephesians chapter five, verse 25 and following.

17:32.765 --> 17:33.626
Ephesians five, 25.

17:35.549 --> 17:38.994
The Bible says for husbands, this means

17:39.202 --> 17:45.149
love your wives just as Christ loved the church.

17:46.831 --> 17:54.501
He gave up his life for her to make her holy and clean washed by the cleansing of God's word.

17:55.362 --> 18:03.912
He did this to present her to himself as a glorious church without a spot or a wrinkle or any other blemish.

18:04.813 --> 18:08.978
Instead, she will be holy and without fault

18:10.338 --> 18:15.827
in the same way husbands ought to love their wives as they love their own bodies.

18:15.867 --> 18:19.733
For a man who loves his wife actually shows love for himself.

18:20.955 --> 18:27.164
No one hates his own body, but he feeds and cares for it just as Christ cares for the church.

18:29.468 --> 18:31.471
Husbands, here it is.

18:32.974 --> 18:34.977
Love like Christ.

18:36.119 --> 18:38.322
Love like Christ.

18:39.490 --> 18:51.484
You know, for years and years, generation, centuries, people have talked about, people in the church have talked about spiritual leadership in the home, resting on the husband.

18:52.285 --> 18:56.750
And there's an element of that that is absolutely accurate and true and good.

18:58.292 --> 19:07.122
But it is imperative, imperative that we understand what spiritual leadership looks like in the context of the gospel.

19:08.258 --> 19:09.260
And it looks like Jesus.

19:10.181 --> 19:16.412
If you want to think about words for husbands, loving like Christ, think about these were two words.

19:17.553 --> 19:20.258
Sacrificial responsibility.

19:21.540 --> 19:23.964
Sacrificial responsibility.

19:27.029 --> 19:29.353
That is your job, husbands.

19:30.615 --> 19:34.802
Women, if you're single and want to be married one day, that's what you're looking for.

19:35.522 --> 19:40.309
You're not looking for somebody who's hot with a big bank account necessarily.

19:41.411 --> 19:51.786
You're looking for someone who is capable of practicing biblical, godly, sacrificial responsibility.

19:53.329 --> 19:56.834
Jesus took responsibility for the church.

19:57.755 --> 20:00.600
Jesus took initiative for the church.

20:00.940 --> 20:04.946
Jesus came and died for the church, gave himself up

20:05.186 --> 20:06.748
before we even knew to ask for it.

20:08.049 --> 20:09.611
Now husbands, think about that for a second.

20:10.752 --> 20:20.984
Think about how many husbands in the room have ever gotten to a sticking point and you didn't know what to say or what to do with your wife.

20:23.527 --> 20:24.308
I mean this morning.

20:28.793 --> 20:29.874
We all get there.

20:32.162 --> 20:42.632
But God calls us to this sacrificial responsibility to love our wives like Christ loves the church.

20:46.335 --> 20:49.819
On my best day, I can't pull that off.

20:50.580 --> 20:52.201
I need help.

20:53.983 --> 20:56.946
Husbands in the room, let's say it together on the count of three.

20:57.606 --> 20:58.907
One, two, three.

20:59.748 --> 21:01.650
I need help.

21:02.690 --> 21:04.332
Let's say it again like we really mean it, okay?

21:05.873 --> 21:07.695
I need help.

21:09.397 --> 21:10.858
I need the help of the Holy Spirit.

21:12.019 --> 21:14.022
I need the help of Scripture.

21:14.542 --> 21:20.228
I need the help of other men who will challenge me and encourage me to be that kind of husband.

21:22.650 --> 21:25.814
To give myself up for Julie.

21:27.595 --> 21:30.258
Can I just tell you, that is not my first step.

21:31.234 --> 21:34.357
That is not my knee-jerk reflex.

21:35.338 --> 21:42.645
When I wake up in the morning, when I go to bed at night, I am not automatically thinking, you know, how could I serve her?

21:44.307 --> 21:47.910
What could I do to make her life easier and better, richer and fuller?

21:49.832 --> 22:00.082
But in those instances when I have listened to the prompting of the Holy Spirit, when I have felt like God's speaking to me, maybe in the middle of an argument, love her like Christ.

22:00.930 --> 22:02.852
Talk to her like Christ would talk to her.

22:03.573 --> 22:10.359
When I have responded to those promptings and done that, everything else gets better.

22:12.081 --> 22:14.824
Every single time.

22:16.345 --> 22:18.848
Sacrificial responsibility.

22:18.868 --> 22:23.793
We take responsibility for the welfare of our brides.

22:24.774 --> 22:26.095
That's what Jesus did for the church.

22:27.596 --> 22:29.138
We take responsibility

22:29.218 --> 22:33.124
for our wives' spiritual health and welfare.

22:33.444 --> 22:38.050
We're leading them by example to say, this is my faith.

22:38.331 --> 22:39.833
This is what I'm learning with Christ.

22:39.853 --> 22:40.794
This is my prayer life.

22:41.235 --> 22:43.218
And I'm sharing this with you.

22:44.700 --> 22:50.688
In God's economy, there is no value, greater or lesser on husband or wife.

22:50.909 --> 22:53.312
There is equal value, but different roles.

22:54.674 --> 22:57.618
And so the role of the husband is sacrificial

22:57.890 --> 22:59.652
responsibility.

23:00.774 --> 23:04.298
That's biblical leadership.

23:06.361 --> 23:13.310
Now, let's take a look at what the Bible says to wives, verses 21 through 24.

23:13.610 --> 23:21.540
It says, and further submit to one another out of reverence for Christ.

23:22.962 --> 23:26.226
For wives, this means submit to your husbands as to the Lord.

23:26.754 --> 23:29.558
Right now, some of you are thinking, I wish I could preach this message.

23:30.619 --> 23:31.901
I wish that was me up there.

23:33.163 --> 23:37.048
But watch this, for a husband is the head of his wife as Christ is the head of the church.

23:37.609 --> 23:40.533
We've already established sacrificial responsibility.

23:40.553 --> 23:43.016
He is the savior of his body, the church.

23:43.036 --> 23:49.525
As the church submits to Christ, so you wives should submit to your husbands in everything.

23:50.326 --> 23:56.434
Wives, go back to verse 21, submit out of reverence for Christ.

23:57.570 --> 24:01.696
Trust Christ through your husband.

24:02.777 --> 24:05.100
Trust Christ through your husband.

24:06.362 --> 24:09.706
Trust that God is in your marriage.

24:10.628 --> 24:15.895
Trust in this supernatural, god-led relationship.

24:16.896 --> 24:17.757
God is at work.

24:19.760 --> 24:27.410
Now, one big advantage that the church has with Christ that you don't have with your husband, the bridegroom of the church is perfect.

24:28.546 --> 24:29.787
your bridegroom ain't.

24:31.349 --> 24:32.411
Somebody like, yeah, tell me.

24:32.791 --> 24:41.942
But you still have the opportunity out of reverence for Christ to submit.

24:41.982 --> 24:55.218
If the keywords for husbands are sacrificial responsibility, the keywords for wives are encouraging goodness, encouraging

24:55.330 --> 24:55.891
Goodness.

24:55.911 --> 24:59.454
That means that you bring goodness to your husband.

25:00.115 --> 25:01.236
Proverbs 31 woman.

25:02.717 --> 25:09.984
Her husband calls her blessed at the city gates and she brings goodness to his life all the days of his life.

25:11.606 --> 25:12.687
She brings goodness.

25:13.588 --> 25:18.933
Remember when God looked at man by himself and he said it's not good for the man to be alone.

25:20.435 --> 25:24.018
To satisfy and solve that dilemma.

25:24.418 --> 25:28.843
He created woman to bring goodness to the man.

25:30.265 --> 25:33.449
You get to be the goodness of God to your husband.

25:36.353 --> 25:37.894
What an incredible gift.

25:38.355 --> 25:39.997
What an incredible opportunity.

25:41.759 --> 25:52.452
Listen, when you encourage your husband, when you fill him with that courage, when you bring that goodness to him, watch him shine.

25:52.572 --> 25:53.874
I've said this for years.

25:54.210 --> 26:00.077
I think of a godly wife is the one who is fanning the flames of God in her husband.

26:00.897 --> 26:01.879
She's fanning the flames.

26:01.899 --> 26:05.042
Now for some of you, it may be just a little glowing ember.

26:06.163 --> 26:09.807
It may be just, you know, get whatever it takes.

26:11.329 --> 26:15.734
But you're feeding the fire of God in the life of your husband.

26:17.856 --> 26:19.218
It's this incredible

26:20.418 --> 26:29.689
back and forth between a husband who serves his wife sacrificially, who takes responsibility for the welfare of their home in every way.

26:30.630 --> 26:35.997
And this wife who encourages, who fills her husband with courage and goodness.

26:37.739 --> 26:49.874
And together, together, they are united into one flesh, one mind, one body, one soul, one life.

26:52.322 --> 27:03.975
And it is this, fanatical focus on the fundamentals that will make a marriage flourish that will make it be everything God wants it to be.

27:04.015 --> 27:14.146
And just to be clear, look at how Ephesians 5 finishes this description of the fundamentals.

27:15.247 --> 27:21.714
It says this is a great mystery, verse 32, but it is an illustration of the way Christ

27:21.890 --> 27:24.493
and the church are one.

27:26.736 --> 27:36.628
See, ultimately marriage, ultimately, foundationally, fundamentally, marriage is not even about husband and wife.

27:38.250 --> 27:43.837
Husband and wife are the vehicles for the gospel and the goodness of God.

27:45.720 --> 27:50.706
And so that's the fire that we feed through this focus on the fundamentals.

27:52.258 --> 27:55.261
I had an opportunity one time that I will never ever forget.

27:55.301 --> 28:06.793
It was a conversation with a woman well into her 80s who she knew was approaching the end of her life.

28:08.495 --> 28:13.680
And so I went into this conversation knowing that it's sacred ground.

28:14.541 --> 28:19.506
It's one of the things that I get to do in my calling as a pastor.

28:21.090 --> 28:24.193
And she began by sharing with me her childhood.

28:25.195 --> 28:26.656
She'd been incredibly challenging.

28:28.018 --> 28:30.460
Her father had died when she was very, very young.

28:30.521 --> 28:35.066
Her mother was unemployed, didn't have a means for supporting the family.

28:35.086 --> 28:36.507
And so she went to live with an aunt.

28:36.527 --> 28:43.975
The aunt and her uncle couldn't sustain and support them.

28:43.996 --> 28:49.842
So she went to an orphanage, an orphanage that was run by

28:50.306 --> 28:52.028
some very harsh people.

28:55.493 --> 29:04.486
But then she pivoted and she said, I have to tell you, I've seen the hand of God in my life so many times.

29:05.427 --> 29:11.316
And I could give you a list, but I will tell you the number one way that I've seen the hand of God in my life.

29:14.680 --> 29:15.622
The husband he gave me.

29:17.705 --> 29:18.706
The husband he gave me.

29:21.794 --> 29:36.136
And as she began to describe her marriage of more than 55 years, I just sat there listening and I just thought, man, God, please one day let Julie say the same thing.

29:37.798 --> 29:50.898
Whatever I do or don't do in this world, please, God, let me be that kind of husband so that at the end of her life, Julie might say, hopefully and prayerfully, you know,

29:51.458 --> 29:53.200
of all the things that I saw God do.

29:56.443 --> 29:57.184
It was my husband.

30:04.872 --> 30:07.134
Marriage is about the gospel.

30:09.737 --> 30:18.706
Marriage is about the good news of Jesus Christ, that Jesus Christ gave himself up, yes for the church, capital C,

30:22.690 --> 30:26.815
But that means for you, by name.

30:28.517 --> 30:32.161
By name, Jesus died for you.

30:33.683 --> 30:36.747
Jesus went to the cross and became your sin.

30:36.807 --> 30:38.589
He became my sin.

30:38.649 --> 30:42.714
And He paid the penalty for our sin so that we don't have to.

30:42.754 --> 30:52.466
The Bible says that the wages of sin, the payoff of sin is death.

30:53.346 --> 31:00.135
The gift of God, the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.

31:00.435 --> 31:05.301
It is the forgiveness of our sins and the life that is truly life.

31:08.205 --> 31:10.067
I wanna ask you to bow your heads for just a moment.

31:12.110 --> 31:21.842
And in this moment, if you have never stepped into that life, you may be here in the room, you may be online,

31:22.114 --> 31:25.798
As a church, we want to give you the opportunity to do just that.

31:27.599 --> 31:31.083
To begin a relationship with God.

31:32.764 --> 31:38.149
To pray a prayer of beginning, a prayer of commitment and submission.

31:39.551 --> 31:44.896
Submission to the one who loves you unconditionally and perfectly.

31:48.759 --> 31:51.602
If that's you, then you pray these words silently right where you are.

31:52.194 --> 31:54.497
Just say, Jesus, I need you.

31:57.361 --> 31:57.882
I need you.

31:57.902 --> 32:06.674
And I believe in this moment that you died on the cross for me, that you rose again from the dead for me.

32:09.037 --> 32:12.823
And in this moment, I accept this gift.

32:16.568 --> 32:18.130
I realize I can't earn it.

32:19.874 --> 32:24.320
I can't do enough good things or not do enough bad things, but it's a gift.

32:28.004 --> 32:28.825
And so I accept.

32:32.130 --> 32:33.471
I commit my life to you.

32:36.355 --> 32:37.917
I confess my sin to you.

32:40.060 --> 32:42.102
And I will follow you from this moment forward.

32:46.848 --> 32:48.210
Lord, I pray this prayer

32:49.314 --> 32:50.195
in your name.

32:57.145 --> 33:13.727
If you would just remain with your heads bowed for another moment, one of the things that we get to do as a church is when someone steps into that relationship with Christ, we get to come alongside and just help with what follows.

33:15.710 --> 33:18.674
And just a moment we'll tell you kind of how

33:18.754 --> 33:24.803
We do that in a way that works for you at your pace as God leads.

33:26.405 --> 33:28.668
But right now, I just want to take a second.

33:29.349 --> 33:33.495
If that was your prayer and you minute, would you just raise your hand?

33:34.917 --> 33:38.061
If you would just raise your hand and hold it up high over your head for a second.

33:40.144 --> 33:47.154
And in this moment, no, that as a church family, we celebrate that with you.

33:47.714 --> 33:56.089
We honor that and our family tradition is you can put your hands down as we put our hands together until you welcome home.

33:56.109 --> 33:56.370
Welcome home.

